{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Listening Quiz: First-Listen Accuracy tracking + per-question replay counter",
  "description": "Add a 'First-Listen Accuracy' metric to the Listening Quiz to discourage endless replays and build true listening comprehension — a core fluency skill. A question is marked 'first-listen' if the user answers it without triggering any replay (sentence playback or full passage replay) after entering the quiz phase.\n\n**Frontend (frontend/src/pages/Listening.tsx)**:\n- Add state `replayCounts: number[]` (length = questions.length, init 0) and `firstListenFlags: boolean[]` (init all true).\n- When entering quiz phase, reset both arrays.\n- In `playSentence` and the full-passage replay handler, if `phase === 'quiz'`, increment `replayCounts[quizIndex]` and set `firstListenFlags[quizIndex] = false`.\n- When user clicks an answer option (in the answer-handler), preserve the current `firstListenFlags[quizIndex]` value at answer time as the question's first-listen status (capture into a parallel `answeredFirstListen: boolean[]`).\n- On the results screen, display a prominent badge near the score: '🎧 First-listen accuracy: X / Y (Z%)' where X = count of questions answered correctly AND first-listen, Y = total questions. Also show per-question 'replayed Nx' subtext under each result row in the existing breakdown panel.\n- Pass `first_listen_correct` and `first_listen_total` (=total_questions) to `saveListeningQuizResult`.\n\n**API (frontend/src/api.ts)**: extend `saveListeningQuizResult` and `ListeningQuizResult` type with optional `first_listen_correct` (number) and `first_listen_total` (number).\n\n**Backend (app/routers/listening.py + app/dal/listening.py)**: extend the save endpoint Pydantic model and DAL insert to accept and persist `first_listen_correct` and `first_listen_total` (default 0). Include them in the row dict returned by history queries (`get_listening_quiz_history`, `get_listening_quiz_detail`).\n\n**Schema (app/database.py)**: add to `listening_quiz_results` CREATE TABLE the columns `first_listen_correct INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0` and `first_listen_total INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0`. Add the following migrations to the END of `_MIGRATIONS`:\n```\n('add first_listen_correct to listening_quiz_results', \"ALTER TABLE listening_quiz_results ADD COLUMN first_listen_correct INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0\"),\n('add first_listen_total to listening_quiz_results', \"ALTER TABLE listening_quiz_results ADD COLUMN first_listen_total INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0\"),\n```\n\n**Tests**: extend existing listening DAL test to verify save+retrieve round-trips the new fields, and an API integration test posting with the new fields.\n\nThis feature gamifies real listening comprehension and gives users a meaningful skill metric distinct from raw quiz score. Variety from recent conversation-heavy iterations (per priority instruction).",
