```json
{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "[PERF] Pre-warm Copilot SDK session at FastAPI startup to cut first-request latency",
  "description": "Per the backlog item '[PERF-HIGH] Conversation response slow (~15s) ... warm pool/connection reuse to cut Session created duplicate (0.7s + 0.1s)', the SDK pays a ~0.7s cost for the very first `client.create_session()` call after startup; subsequent session creations within the same process are cheaper (~0.1s) because the SDK reuses an underlying connection. Today the first user-facing /api/conversation/start or /api/conversation/message therefore eats this cold-start ~0.6s on top of the LLM time, and even a single restart re-introduces it. This change pre-warms the SDK on FastAPI startup so real user traffic always hits the warm path.\n\nChanges:\n\n1. `app/copilot_client.py` — add an `async def prewarm(self) -> None` method on `CopilotService` that:\n   - calls `await self._ensure_client()` (already cached-safe), then\n   - creates a throwaway session with a tiny system message (`SystemMessageReplaceConfig(mode='replace', content='ping')`) using `self._model` and an auto-approve permission callback (mirroring `ask`),\n   - immediately calls `await session.destroy()`.\n   - Wrap the entire body in try/except: log a warning and swallow any exception (prewarm must NEVER block startup). Log the elapsed wall-clock time so we can observe the cold-start cost in production.\n   - Idempotency: guard with an `self._prewarmed: bool` flag so repeated calls during tests are no-ops.\n\n2. `app/main.py` — inside the existing `lifespan` context manager, after `await init_db()` and `start_wal_checkpoint_task()`, schedule prewarm as a background task using `asyncio.create_task(get_copilot_service().prewarm())` so startup is NOT blocked (the FastAPI app must accept traffic immediately even if Copilot auth is slow). Keep a reference to the task on `app.state.copilot_prewarm_task` so it isn't garbage-collected, and on shutdown best-effort `await asyncio.wait_for(task, timeout=0.1)` swallowing TimeoutError before closing the service.\n\n3. `tests/unit/test_copilot_prewarm.py` — new file with two tests using a `CopilotService` instance whose `_ensure_client` and session creation are monkeypatched with `AsyncMock`s:\n   - `test_prewarm_creates_and_destroys_session`: assert `_ensure_client` called once, `client.create_session` called once with `model=self._model` and a `SystemMessageReplaceConfig` whose `content == 'ping'`, and `session.destroy` awaited once.\n   - `test_prewarm_swallows_exceptions`: make `create_session` raise; assert `prewarm()` returns normally (no exception propagated) and the warning is logged.\n   - `test_prewarm_is_idempotent`: call prewarm twice; assert `create_session` called only once.\n\nNo schema changes. No config.yaml changes. Total: 3 files modified (one new test file). Keeps the change small and easily verifiable, while delivering a measurable ~0.5s reduction on the first user-facing conversation request after every server restart.",
  "files_to_modify": ["app/copilot_client.py", "app/main.py", "tests/unit/test_copilot_prewarm.py"],
  "priority": "high",
  "estimated_complexity": "small"
}
