Starting iteration 636. Dispatching proposer.

Based on the explicit backlog item PERF-HIGH (conversation 応答遅い) and unaddressed sub-options (warm pool, parallelize feedback+reply already done in #625/#626/#635), the remaining high-leverage win is **session warm-pool**. Logs in `copilot_client.ask()` show session creation is timed separately from LLM and is a meaningful chunk of the 15s budget. Pre-creating the next session in the background after each call eliminates that cost on the next request.

```json
{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Copilot session warm-pool to cut conversation /message latency",
  "description": "Address backlog item [PERF-HIGH] (Conversation 応答遅い). Per the existing log line in app/copilot_client.py CopilotService.ask() — `Session created (%.1fs)` — the SDK's `client.create_session(...)` step is reported separately from the LLM `send_and_wait` time and contributes a non-trivial portion of the 15s p95. We already pre-warmed the SDK client (#634) and parallelized start (#625) / end (#626) / skip-grammar-trivial (#635). The remaining unimplemented sub-option from the backlog is a warm pool.\n\nImplementation (single backend file + one test file):\n1. In `app/copilot_client.py`, extend `CopilotService` with a tiny session warm-pool:\n   - Add `self._warm_session: Any | None = None` and `self._warm_lock = asyncio.Lock()`.\n   - Add `async def _take_warm_session(self, system_prompt: str) -> tuple[Any, bool]`: under the lock, pop `self._warm_session` (if any) and return `(session, True)`. The caller will still need a session whose system message matches `system_prompt`. Because Copilot SDK creates the session with `SystemMessageReplaceConfig(mode='replace', content=system_prompt)`, we cannot reuse a session with a different system prompt directly. Instead, treat the warm session as a session pre-created with NO system message override, and pass the system prompt at session.send_and_wait time IF the SDK supports per-message override; if not, fall back to creating a fresh session.\n   - Simpler/safer alternative (preferred): treat the warm pool as a **session-creation lookahead**. In `ask()`, AFTER `await session.destroy()` in the `finally` block, schedule a background task `asyncio.create_task(self._prewarm_session())` that pre-creates a placeholder session (system_prompt=' ') and stores it in `self._warm_session`. In the next `ask()` call, if `self._warm_session is not None` AND the SDK supports replacing the system message via a second `SystemMessageReplaceConfig` send (verify via a try/except), use it; otherwise destroy it and create fresh. Net effect: even when reuse fails, the next call's session creation runs in parallel with prior I/O — but on the success path we save 1-3s.\n   - If runtime testing shows the SDK rejects system-message replacement on an existing session, fall back to a pure parallelism win: kick off `client.create_session(...)` BEFORE building prompts in `send_message` (router-level prefetch), and await it where `ask()` currently calls it. This still saves wall-clock by overlapping session creation with prompt assembly + DB reads.\n\n2. Add a per-label latency record so we can see the p50 improvement: in `LatencyTracker.record`, additionally track `session_s` (it already does — confirm). Log the p50 of `session_s` alongside llm/total in the existing periodic log at `_REPORT_EVERY=20`.\n\n3. Add `app/__init__.py` shutdown hook (or extend existing FastAPI shutdown in `app/main.py`) to destroy any warm session on app shutdown to avoid leaks. (1-line addition, only if main.py already has a shutdown handler — otherwise skip.)\n\n4. Tests in `tests/unit/test_copilot_warm_pool.py`:\n   - Mock `CopilotClient` and `client.create_session` to count invocations.\n   - Assert that after one `ask()` call, a background warm session is created (await `asyncio.sleep(0)` to let the task run).\n   - Assert that the second `ask()` consumes the warm session (no extra `create_session` call on the hot path) OR, in the fallback mode, that `create_session` is started before `send_and_wait` and is awaited inline.\n   - Assert latency tracker now reports `session_s` p50 in the periodic log (capture log output).\n\nNo schema changes. No config changes. Single backend module + one test file.",
  "files_to_modify": ["app/copilot_client.py", "app/main.py", "tests/unit/test_copilot_warm_pool.py"],
  "priority": "high",
  "estimated_complexity": "medium"
}
