  "title": "Shadowing progress badge — show attempts, avg & best score on Shadowing page",
  "description": "Add a small motivational progress badge to the Quick Shadowing Drill so users can see their cumulative practice and improvement at a glance. Currently `app/routers/shadowing.py` only returns per-attempt feedback and never surfaces aggregate progress, so users have no sense of momentum between sessions.\n\nBackend (no schema changes — uses existing `shadowing_attempts` table):\n1. In `app/dal/shadowing.py`, add `async def get_stats(db) -> dict[str, Any]` that returns: `total_attempts` (int, COUNT(*)), `avg_combined_last_20` (float, AVG((accuracy+timing_score)/2.0) over the 20 most recent rows ordered by created_at DESC, id DESC; rounded to 1 decimal; 0.0 when no rows), `best_combined` (float, MAX((accuracy+timing_score)/2.0); 0.0 when no rows), and `last_attempt_at` (ISO string or null). Implement with a single SELECT for totals and a subquery/CTE for the last-20 average so it stays one round trip.\n2. In `app/routers/shadowing.py`, add a `ShadowingStatsResponse` Pydantic model and a `GET /api/shadowing/stats` endpoint that calls the DAL and returns the response. Return zeros / null when there are no attempts (do not 404).\n\nFrontend:\n3. In `frontend/src/api.ts`, export `type ShadowingStats` and `getShadowingStats(): Promise<ShadowingStats>` (GET `/api/shadowing/stats`).\n4. In `frontend/src/pages/Shadowing.tsx`, fetch stats once on mount (and refresh after each successful `submitShadowingAttempt`). Render a compact badge near the page header showing: `Attempts: N · Avg (last 20): X.X · Best: Y.Y`. Hide the avg/best chips when `total_attempts === 0` and instead show a friendly hint (\"Your progress will appear here after your first attempt\"). Keep styling consistent with existing badges; ensure dark-mode classes are applied.\n\nTests:\n5. Add `tests/unit/test_shadowing_stats.py` (new file) covering the DAL `get_stats`: empty table returns zeros and null timestamp; after inserting 3 attempts via `record_attempt`, totals/avg/best/last_attempt_at are correct; after inserting 25 attempts with varying scores, `avg_combined_last_20` only averages the 20 most recent and `best_combined` reflects the global maximum (not just last 20). Use the existing in-memory db fixture pattern from other DAL tests.\n\nAcceptance: new endpoint returns 200 with correct shape; Shadowing page renders the badge; tests pass.",
