{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Conversation Quick Reply mode (1-sentence AI replies, ~50% faster p50)",
  "description": "Adds a user-facing 'Quick Reply' mode to /conversation that drastically lowers AI response latency by constraining the LLM to a single short reply (the dominant cost of conversation latency is generation tokens). This directly addresses the PERF-HIGH backlog item with a fresh angle (output-token reduction) that is independent of the already-shipped warm-pool, lifespan pre-warm, parallel grammar-call, and trivial-skip work.\n\nBackend (app/routers/conversation.py, app/dal/conversation.py, app/database.py):\n1. Add `quick_mode: bool = False` to `StartRequest`.\n2. Persist on the conversations row. Schema change in `database.py` SCHEMA: add `quick_mode INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0` to the `conversations` CREATE TABLE. REQUIRED migration (append to `_MIGRATIONS` in database.py): `\"ALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN quick_mode INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0\"`.\n3. Update `conv_dal.create_conversation` to accept and store `quick_mode`; ensure `get_active_conversation` / row dict-conversion exposes the column (already implicit via SELECT *).\n4. In both `start_conversation` and `send_message`, when `conv.quick_mode` is true, append this instruction to the system prompt:  `\"\\nIMPORTANT: Reply with ONE short sentence only (max 18 words). Be natural and conversational, but never use multiple sentences.\"`\n5. In `send_message`, when quick_mode is true, also force-skip the grammar-check call (treat like trivial message) — this is opt-in by the user and avoids an entire parallel LLM call. Log `Quick Mode: grammar check skipped`.\n6. Include `quick_mode` in `StartResponse` so the frontend can confirm.\n\nFrontend (frontend/src/pages/Conversation.tsx, frontend/src/api.ts):\n1. Add `quick_mode?: boolean` to `startConversation` API params and to the StartResponse type.\n2. Add a small toggle (⚡ Quick Reply) in the pre-start panel near the difficulty/personality selectors with a tooltip: \"Faster, snappier replies (1 sentence). Great for rapid speaking drills.\"\n3. Pass the toggle value to `api.startConversation`. Persist the user's choice in localStorage so it survives reloads.\n4. While the conversation is active, show a small ⚡ badge in the header when quick mode is on.\n\nTesting (tests/unit/test_conversation_dal.py or new tests/integration/test_conversation_quick_mode.py):\n- DAL test: `create_conversation(..., quick_mode=True)` round-trips correctly.\n- Integration test: `POST /api/conversation/start` with `quick_mode=true` returns it in the response and persists it; subsequent `POST /api/conversation/message` skips grammar check (assert feedback is None and only ONE LLM call is made by mocking copilot).\n\nMeasurable outcome: log p50 of `conversation_message` label before/after (existing latency tracker). Expected ~30-50% p50 reduction when quick_mode=true because (a) only 1 LLM call instead of 2 in parallel and (b) shorter generated output.",
  "files_to_modify": ["app/routers/conversation.py", "app/dal/conversation.py", "app/database.py", "frontend/src/pages/Conversation.tsx", "frontend/src/api.ts"],
  "priority": "high",
  "estimated_complexity": "medium"
}
